				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If it was 60 pts per mob solo, it is 10 pts per mob for full group, add 80% to that is only18 each right?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Actually for a full group it will only be divided by 5, so base will be 12 * 80% = 21.6
<br />

<br />
Another thing to take into account is downtime.  The downtime for a person to solo something is going to be much greater then a full group fighting the same mob(s).  In this case, the full group only has to kill things at three times the rate of a solo person to see experience benefits over soloing.  (If they kill 3 mobs in the time it takes a solo'er to kill one, everyone in the group gets 64.8 points... the soloer only gets 60).<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://scrubfire.dyndns.org/KJ_Sig.jpg" border="0" />
