			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Lemee break it down further, see if i get it right
<br />

<br />
120% / 2 members = 60% per member (1.4 mobs to pass soloing)
<br />
140% / 3 members = 46.66% per member (2.14 mobs to pass soloing)
<br />
160% / 4 members = 40% per member (2.5 mobs to pass soloing)
<br />
180% / 5 members = 36% per member (2.78 mobs to pass soloing)
<br />

<br />
6 members get 180% bonus, but is split like 5 members. So depending how you look at it:
<br />
180% / 6 members = 30% per member, PLUS 6% bonus
<br />
180% / 6 members = 180% / 5 members = 36%
<br />

<br />
Yikes.
<br />

<br />
On the flip side, soloing to 65 (as a mage) is now a lot more feasible, but at the same time still a lot slower than grouping.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/xalsig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by XalmatElemental on Wed May 28, 2003 3:17 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
